cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generative modeling of shapes. It could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves synthesizing shapes. The use of deep neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the focus on generating "unseen" data suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the introduction of quantitative metrics to evaluate the generative model suggests that it could also belong to the software engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
